    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-02T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-02T01:35:00-05:00" n="614"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/566: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-02T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 2, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>573. Millspaugh suggests that if the credit requested is approved it be made
                    conditional on approval of his taxation proposals now pending in the Majlis.
                    This support would probably ensure their passage as well as provide greater
                    security for the credit. This telegram is in reference to my 484, May 10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
